After a while both users decide to leave the session. Apart from calling 
leaveSession()
 (and therefore 
session.disconnect()
) to destroy the connection on OpenVidu Server, we need to run the last POST operation: we must let the backend know that certain user has left the session so it can update the collections with the active sessions and tokens. To sum up, 
session.disconnect()
 updates our OpenVidu Server and the POST operation updates our application's backend.
For the POST operation, in 
app.js
 we run:


function removeUser() {
    httpPostRequest(
        'api-sessions/remove-user',
