To launch multiple apps in the same instance, just store each one of them inside its own folder under  /opt/ . For example:   /opt/YOUR_APP_1  : will be available at  https://AMAZON_URL_OR_YOUR_CUSTOM_DOMAIN/YOUR_APP_1/  /opt/YOUR_APP_2  : will be available at  https://AMAZON_URL_OR_YOUR_CUSTOM_DOMAIN/YOUR_APP_2/   The other steps explained above also need some adjustments related to paths:    Configure Nginx: now it would be...  location /YOUR_APP_1 {
  rewrite /YOUR_APP_1(.*) /$1 break;
  proxy_pass https://localhost:PORT1;
}

location /YOUR_APP_2 {
  rewrite /YOUR_APP_2(.*) /$1 break;
  proxy_pass https://localhost:PORT2;
}    Configure Supervisor: now...    [program:YOUR_APP_1]
  command=/bin/bash /opt/YOUR_APP_1/YOUR_LAUNCHER_1.sh YOUR_APP1_PARAM_1 YOUR_APP1_PARAM_2 ...
  redirect_stderr=true

  [program:YOUR_APP_2]
